Requirements

We would love to have you on our team if you have any of the following, but don’t worry too much if you don’t meet all the requirements:

5+ years experience in data engineering and data warehouse/lake design, with specific experience working in Snowflake, dbt, AWS, Terraform and FiveTran or equivalents.
Experience in managing relationships with stakeholders, gathering requirements and balancing tactical and strategic aspects of evolving a healthy data warehouse.
Deep understanding of ETL and data modeling concepts and patterns. Proficiency with SQL, Python, Spark and TypeScript are a plus.
Experience working with AWS services including S3 and Sagemaker, and integrating them with Snowflake.
Experience with DataOps/DevSecOps principles and practices (e.g. Github Actions, Terraform Cloud, CDK)
2+ years of experience working with Tableau Desktop and Tableau Online environments. A bonus if you have experience working with Snowflake alongside Tableau.
Familiarity with architectural patterns and best practices, especially those associated with BI solutions.
Thrive in a fast-paced, sometimes unpredictable, and highly collaborative work environment spread across the globe
Bachelor's or Master's Degree in computer science, physics, math, or a related field
